  "prompt": "What are the top ten PC games ever?",
  "response": "Determining the top ten PC games ever is highly subjective and can vary based on personal preferences, critical acclaim, and impact on the gaming industry. However, I can provide a list of ten influential and widely acclaimed PC games that are often cited as some of the best:\n\n1. **Half-Life 2 (2004)** - Known for its groundbreaking physics engine, engaging storytelling, and immersive gameplay, Half-Life 2 is a staple in the first-person shooter genre.\n\n2. **The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt (2015)** - Celebrated for its deep narrative, expansive open world, and complex characters, The Witcher 3 remains a benchmark for modern RPGs.\n\n3. **Portal (2007)** - This puzzle-platformer is praised for its innovative mechanics, clever writing, and the memorable AI antagonist, GLaDOS.\n\n4. **StarCraft (1998)** - As a cornerstone of the real-time strategy genre, StarCraft has had a lasting impact on esports and multiplayer gaming dynamics.\n\n5. **World of Warcraft (2004)** - An MMORPG that revolutionized the genre, creating a vast world filled with intricate lore and community-driven content.\n\n6. **Minecraft (2011)** - A sandbox game that encourages creativity and exploration, Minecraft has become a cultural phenomenon with its simple yet addictive gameplay.\n\n7. **The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim (2011)** - Known for its vast open world and flexibility in player choice, Skyrim has maintained a strong player base through mods and re-releases.\n\n8. **Doom (1993)** - A pioneering title in the first-person shooter genre, Doom set the standard for future FPS games and continues to be a cultural icon.\n\n9. **Civilization IV (2005)** - Although various entries in the series are beloved, Civilization IV is often praised for its depth and addictive turn-based strategy gameplay.\n\n10. **Deus Ex (2000)** - A groundbreaking blend of first-person action and RPG elements, Deus Ex is known for its deep story, player choice, and cyberpunk setting.\n\nThis list could vary greatly depending on the criteria used for evaluation, such as gameplay mechanics, story, innovation, or cultural impact. Different players and critics may prioritize different aspects of what makes a game \"great.\"",
